{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Yc8eHWfDGh9X3LWEx8WKfZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The replica set hasn't been initiated yet. The issue with starting MongoDB with `--auth` is that we can't authenticate until we create a user, but we can't create a user until we authenticate (chicken-and-egg problem). However, MongoDB has a special \"localhost exception\" that allows you to connect from localhost without authentication before any users are created.\n\nSo the process should be:\n1. Connect to pod 0 via localhost (exec into the pod)\n2. Initiate the replica set (rs.initiate())\n3. Wait for PRIMARY to be elected\n4. Create the admin user using the localhost exception\n5. Then create the app user\n\nBut the current setup already has `--auth` from the start, and `MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME` is set. \n\nThe problem is that by overriding the `command` in the StatefulSet to run `mongod` directly instead of using the Docker entrypoint, we're bypassing the initialization script that would normally handle the `MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME` env var. That script temporarily starts MongoDB without auth, creates the root user, then restarts with auth enabled.\n\nWith `--auth` and `--keyFile` together, the localhost exception still applies for creating the first admin user, so I can connect to the first pod without authentication, initiate the replica set, and then create both the admin and application users before the other replicas join.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":204,"cache_read_input_tokens":40085,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":204},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"859a51aa-2b33-4760-bb78-ab3e52b75fb7","uuid":"97e467ce-c542-476c-af2c-91f3448ea034","request_id":"req_011CcLS96CT9KjhojDzX3Y29"}
